The paper deals with wireless powered cognitive radio networks, which involve wireless power transfer, spectrum sensing, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves network infrastructure and protocols, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a new frame structure and optimization problems, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves compressive sensing and matrix completion techniques, which fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves optimization problems, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
